{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"norm-dam-swab","description":"## Why\nEpic 88ab (elfish-chair-lug) S6. The pattern's known failure mode is branch rot (OpenDev warns feature branches are \"not for sustained long term development\"; Qt abandoned routine long-lived-branch merges) — so lifetime/cadence policy and a tested back-out must exist, and the cost claims (re-reviews avoided vs CI re-runs incurred) must be measured, not asserted.\n\n## What\n- Branch-lifetime cap + catch-up merge cadence documented (policy lives with the S4 CONTRIBUTING section; this story owns the policy content + the inventory tooling).\n- Stale-branch inventory: a scripted check (infra/scripts or infra/gerrit) flags `feature/*` branches inactive beyond the cap — merged-back OR abandoned — for owner-confirmed deletion; recorded in the runbook.\n- Back-out documented + TESTED on the live Gerrit: revoke pushMerge + feature/* ACLs restores the single-change-only flow (\"no label/gate changes REQUIRED\" — the copyCondition addition is inert absent merge changes and may be left or reverted); submit-type pin back-out = remove the [submit] block and confirm the inherited value matches the S1-recorded prior state; bot code back-out = redeploy the prior review-bot image.\n- \"Cost & latency\" section in the amending ADR, from the S5 runs: median CI wall-clock per merge change; count of LLM re-reviews avoided via MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE carry vs CI re-runs incurred across scenarios; per-review LLM cost if surfaced by the runner.\n\n## Scope\nPolicy + tooling + measurements. Depends on S5 (run data) and the S1-recorded submit-type prior state. No new gate/bot behavior.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Lifetime cap + cadence policy written and referenced from CONTRIBUTING/runbook\n- [ ] Stale-branch inventory script committed + runbook entry (flag + owner-confirmed delete; covers abandoned branches)\n- [ ] Back-out tested live: ACL revoke restores single-change flow; submit-type revert verified against the S1-recorded value; bot rollback path documented\n- [ ] ADR \"Cost & latency\" section populated with the three named metrics from S5 data","id":"72b8-4cda-ccd4-414d","parent_id":"88ab-7052-8850-46d4","priority":2,"tags":["gerrit","feature-branch","process","runbook"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"S6: Process policy + back-out + cost/latency record for the feature-branch flow"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782964899388001001,"uuid":"63744742-a6ac-4e8b-8c62-950687a46807"}